    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3,
                                1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: Referring to my note of the 31st
                            ultimo, and in reply to yours of yesterday, I have the honor to confirm
                            all that I said with respect to the request of the firm of E. Atkins
                            &amp; Co., and I take pleasure in informing you that these gentlemen
                            have repeatedly expressed to me their satisfaction with the zeal and
                            energy with which the Spanish authorities of the Island of Cuba endeavor
                            to protect their property and interests from the attacks of the
                            insurgents.</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
